50|$|Stock options under International Financial Reporting Standards are {{addressed}} by IFRS 2 Share-based Payments. For transactions with employees and others providing similar services, the entity {{is required to}} measure the fair value of the <b>equity</b> <b>instruments</b> granted at the grant date. In the absence of market prices, fair value is estimated using a valuation technique to estimate what the price of those <b>equity</b> <b>instruments</b> {{would have been on}} the measurement date in an arm's length transaction between knowledgeable, willing parties. The standard does not specify which particular model should be used.|$|R
