40|$|This study's {{underlying}} {{premise is}} that current pension plan accounting has two important negative effects. First, it distorts the measurement of earnings and net worth in the short run, {{as well as the}} pattern of earnings over future periods. Second, this distortion can send incorrect signals to investors about a firm's health, resulting in the mispricing of a firm's outstanding debt and <b>equity</b> <b>instruments.</b> The author demonstrates how these distortions are introduced, examines the magnitude of the distortions, and discusses proposals for reform...|$|R
